A Brief Examination of their History
Most scholars agree that Alraunes and Myconids are the
result of long gone blood mages on Amirian Island
tampering with the natural world, as there is no real
history to their species, they just appeared one day
around 800 years ago. First spotted in the forests
south of Dawn Harbor, Alraunes and Myconids have slowly
spread across the land, and can now be found in the
vast majority of forests and swamps around the continent.
While Alraunes and Myconids seem to have come from
the same place, there are quite different in nature,
although both creatures are plant based.
Alraunes are the more dangerous of the two.
They appear in the form of an alluring woman atop a
red/maroon flower. The “woman” in question is green
skinned and red haired, with deep black eyes and small
red pupils, and is almost always around 5’9” in height,
although her legs are obfuscated by the flower,
making it hard to size up most Alraunes from a distance.
An Alraune usually relies on its special ability to
capture prey: a soothing odor that will render the prey
incapable of making any hostile acts against it.
If the odor takes effect, the Alraune is free to attack
its foe, as the calming scent can wipe away any
thoughts of violence from its prey. While an Alraune
is asleep, it appears to merely be a large plant with
a single large flower at its center, as its feminine
form is folded into the plant itself. Regardless of the
plant’s apparent femininity, it is itself asexual and
reproduces (usually once or twice every 4-6 years) by
budding a single offspring over the course of the summer
Alraunes are quite mobile, and are more than capable of
running 8-12mph like a spider upon their numerous long
vines in order to chase down potential prey,
preferring humanoid flesh over all others.
Take care when traveling in forests and swamps without
backup, because if an Alraune decides to chase you down,
you’ll need all the help you can get.
Myconids resemble normal redcap fungi and can range in
height, from 2-6 feet in most cases.
I say “normal redcap fungi”, but Myconids look very
feminine, with a soft, gentle face, purple hair and
slender body. Myconids are quite unique amongst the
Basidiomycota races for their complete aversion to
violent behavior. While they distrust outsiders,
they will avoid conflict, and simply move away from
the adventurer or hunter in question. Despite their
proclivity to suspicion, they will sometimes offer
shelter or allow passage through their colonies to
some of those who approach their territory, although
why they show this behavior is not known, as it seems
random, and all studies that have tried to figure out
why have been unsuccessful. Myconids are not always
peaceful however, and can be quite violent if serving
an Alraune. Why some Myconids serve Alraunes is not
known at this time, although some scholars believe
that the blood mages may have engineered this behavior.
There is a mutant strain of Myconid that also has a
tendency towards violence, so just because an Alraune
is not around doesn’t mean you can let your guard down.
One easy way to tell if a Myconid is “normal” or “mutant”
is to look at their cap, and their eyes.
A mutant Myconids cap is all red, with no yellow or
black spots, while their eyes are bright yellow.
If you come across one, use fire to scare it off or
kill it, as fire is the Myconids natural weakness.
Myconids grow up in four stages,
When first spawned, Myconid infants are only a few
inches tall and look like normal red cap mushrooms.
They lack any method of self-preservation, and furthermore
are not self-aware at this stage. Four-year-old myconids
are 1-2 feet tall, and are fully capable of intelligent
thought and movement. At eight years old, myconids go
through a growth spurt, and will grow 3-5 feet.
They will also gain the ability to reproduce via spores,
and will do so once every two years (usually a total
of fours times). By 12 years, they will begin to rapidly
fade in both strength and height, and by 16, they are dead.
Alraunes and Myconids are truly one of a kind, while
their origins are somewhat artificial, they are the pure
embodiment of nature itself in many ways:
and in the case of Alraunes, very, very green.
A Brief Examination of their History
The beast kin race is a rather diverse one,
unlike slimes or goos for example, beast kin are not
uniform at all. From the dark age, when chaos ruled and
the Dark One was cast out, all the way to present day,
As far as origins go, they evolved much in the same way
that humans or elves did, starting as hunch-backed,
barbaric monsters before slowing gaining intelligence
and walking more upright. There is no such thing as a
"typical" or "standard" beast kin, and they appear to
share traits akin to certain species of animals.
It is from here that they derive their striking appearance.
While a combination of an upright, humanoid stature with
a mixture of mammalian fur, claws and fangs could look
rather frightening at first glance, beast kin are by
and large not to be feared. They are no more predisposed
to war than you or me. Currently, there are only three
They seem to take their animalistic traits from the
great white bears of the north, the cunning leopards
that lay in wait in the snow, and the fierce, unyielding
wolves that ravage the frozen lands.
As far as their physiology is concerned, this was a
point of great interest for researchers and scholars
for many years, as the mystery of just where it was
they got their animalist traits from was a mystery,
and was only confirmed rather recently, around 80 years
Within their territory, the tribes of beast kin display
great feats that are beyond that of humans.
There are old writings that suggest that exceptional
youths of the bear tribe showed strength enough to rival
Meanwhile, members of the leopard tribe have been known
to take down mounted scouts at full gallop while on foot.
Most frightening of all are the wolves, as scores of
men in ancient full and half plate armor have been
discovered with striking bite and claw marks in them,
rending the armor into little more than splinters.
Curiously enough however, there are scant few tales of
beast kin outside of the north.
While enticing images of man-beasts shattering full
armor with a single hit is interesting, most exciting
of all perhaps is their ability to cultivate the frozen
soil of the north. While they may seem at first to be
creatures that exist purely on a diet of meat,
they are in reality, omnivores, a fact that takes many
by surprise. This cultivation is a feat not yet equaled
by any save for the humans who live on the natural
southern borders where there is more sun and water to
work with.  Perhaps it is due to their unnatural
strength and endurance, no one knows for sure,
as it is yet to discovered how exactly they do it.
While they have a chosen group of hunters go out to
gather wildlife, it is not random, as they only hunt in
their own established territories. This is only done to
complement their harvest, and is not a replacement for
This brings us to the delicate relationship between the
three tribes and the humans that live in the southern
Having observed a handful of meetings between those of
the hunter classification, things were tense to say the
least. Although no blows were struck, there was a great
deal of posturing, threats made in the Common tongue
and eventually a mutual parting.  Border disputes are
apparently quite common between the three tribes,
with warriors clashing during patrols whenever they meet.
All three tribes adhere to a strict code of honor and
do not slay their adversaries, opting to capture them
to gain information in order to gain advantages for
future attacks before releasing them back to their
lands to receive punishment. Humans, on the other hand,
are regarded as outsiders and treated as little more
Should they be unfortunate enough to wander into these
toyed with, and if they bore their captors,
Be it elves, humans, or demi-humans, the mortal races
of the land are never fully peaceful.
While no major wars have been fought in some time,
there are those that believe we are overdue for conflict.
I sure hope I don’t have to fight a beast kin.
A Brief Examination of their History
Imps are very old creatures, and existed many thousands
of years ago during the time of the Great Evil.
Many imps sided with the Great Evil when he invaded the
lands of mortals, and turned red as a result of the
Some records indicate that they were once very tall and
strong, but that time has long since passed, and imps
are no taller than 2.0’ in 99% of all documented
Imps are usually weak and non-threatening, as their
small stature leaves them with no imposing figure,
and no strength to weld powerful weapons.
Imps come in three varieties, and are not all tainted
by evil’s influence. In fact, Imps come in three known
colors, with two more being reported, but not confirmed.
These are: Green, White, Red, Black, and Purple.
Greens are by far the most common, as well as the least
threatening. Green Imps are mostly found in forests and
around lakes and streams, and are not know to attack
They are known to steal things from unwary travelers
who camp to close to their den, but the people
The Green Imp is an omnivore, just like its White
skinned cousin, and can be seen eating berries, roots,
If you come across a large group of them, don’t yell
or run, as that can agitate them, instead, simply back
away slowly and let them continue on their way.
White Imps are rarer than their green-skinned
compatriots, but they are still seen regularly by
They tend to live in the Northern, mountainous regions
of the continent, around 8,500 meters above sea level.
For those of you that remember my writings on the
Beast-Kin, you’ll know that the Beast-Kin tribes tend
to live along the Eastern side of the Ari-Mur Ridge
around 7,000 meters above sea level, as such, Beast-Kin
and White Imps rarely fight over resources.
They tend to be shy creatures, and will only fight if
cornered, as such, it is recommended that anybody that
comes across one simply still their distance, as that
alone will be enough to avoid an encounter.
Like Green Imps, Whites are omnivores, and will eat
just about anything that will give them nutrients.
It is said by some Human Shamans and Beast-Kin
Spirtweavers that White Imp Chieftains will sometimes
bestow skills and power to adventures that they deem
The validity of those claims has yet to be determined.
They are violent, savage little beasts and will attack
They are a demonic variety of the green imp,
and are under control of the Great Evil.
Most were killed many eons ago, after the purge that
occurred after the Battle of Bloodstone Gulch,

Goblins are the younger, rambunctious cousins of Imps.
While Imps are short and quiet, Goblins are short and

Goblins tend to stand no higher than 3 feet, and are
While Imps don’t appear to have the mental faculties
for tool making, goblins can fashion stone tools and
weapons, as well as traps such as snares, which they
use to hunt many forms of small game.
While Imps are omnivores, goblins tend to be carnivores,
as their superior intellect allows them to hunt a far
They are also far more aggressive in nature, and they
will attack adventurers and farmhands alike with no
warning. Because they are short, they can easily hide
under long grass in groups of two or three and strike
from the victims right and left flank, sometimes capable
of taking even a well-equipped foe down. Because of
the danger goblins can pose, and the frequency at which
they breed, adventurer groups are regularly paid quite
handsome sums of money to clean out nests of goblins
every few months by the local governments.
While it seems impossible to fully eradicate goblins,
this system has worked to force goblins deeper and
deeper underground each year, and the further

Because of the overwhelming opposition goblins face by
the other mortal races, seeing a goblin above ground is
quite the rarity, they may be found deep in forests,
in old towers and run down towns, although this is
quite rare, as about 98% of all goblin nests are now
found in caves and old dungeons long abandoned.
Unlike Imps and Elves, goblins as a species were
never actually tainted by the Great Evil, contrary to
what old folk tales and legends would have you believe,
as the Great Evil was already defeated and cast out of
the mortal plane years before goblins ever came to be.
In fact, goblins have fought with the races created by
the Great Evil many times over the past few millennia.
Dark elves and goblins have fought no less than 6 wars
with one another over land and resources.

Goos are close relatives of slimes, and share much of
the same physiology. They both have a double transport
system for respiration, they both have no internal
skeleton or exoskeleton, they are both hermaphrodites,
and they both have a peripheral nervous system,
The one major difference, is that Slimes are specialized
ambush predators, while goos are pack hunters.
Because goos are much faster than slimes, they tend to
hunt different prey. While Slimes will usually kill
smaller prey quickly, goos opt to run their prey down
slowly over large distances, wearing them out,
cornering them, and striking them down with their small
barbed limb, known as a “lady finger”.
This small barb transmits a fast acting neurotoxin that
causes paralysis in just 10 minutes. Once this has set

nothing left, as they even digest bone.

the Great Evil spread across the world.
It’s debated that exactly the Great Evil was,
some believe it was an Arch-Demon,
while others think it may have been a Kraken,
the size of a city. Whatever it was, it scoured the
country-side, claiming young maidens of all races,
adding them to his collection of tickle slaves.
The High Elves of the Kingdom of Lys were conquered
by the Great Evil, and subjugated,
He corrupted them, turning their skin black,
their hair silver-white, and their eyes, blood red.
He called them “Dark Elves” and sent them out to defeat
the human kingdoms of the River lands.
This was known as the First Dark Elf War.
According to the records we have available,
there were Three Dark Elf Wars in total,
But, at last, the Great Evil was cast down and defeated
at the Battle of Bloodstone Gulch,
and the Dark Elves were enslaved by the other
mortal races for the next millennia.
